<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06019157 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06019157 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  IRAQ; KUWAIT; MIDEAST; WAR; US; CITY; BOMB; NEWS; VIDEO  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  An ABC cameraman who obtained rare footage of the first hours of the alliedbombing of Baghdad said Friday that he shot the dramatic film while hanginghalfway out the seventh-floor window of his downtown hotel room.;    CameramanFabrice Moussus managed to escape with it into Jordan.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  BOMBING FOOTAGE WAS HARD TO GET  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  War in the GulfSee related stories pages 1A and 17-28A of this section.  </MEMO><TEXT>     The network first aired the film at 7:07 p.m. PST Thursday, showing theBaghdad skyline alight with anti-aircraft fire and allied bombs.;    Moussus,a cameraman with ABC for 10 years, had previously shot exclusive footage ofthe assassination of Egyptian president Anwar Sadat in 1981, according to RenaTerracuso, a network spokeswoman.;    Moussus, speaking from Amman, Jordan,told ABC that he and a sound man shot the nearly three hours of bombingfootage using a night scope to enhance the images.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  New York  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  SAN JOSE MERCURY NEWS  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910119  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Saturday  </DAY><MONTH>  January  </MONTH><PG.COL>  18A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  144  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Saturday January 19, 199100019157,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>